Class Ellipsoid

All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Equivalency, GeodeticObject, NamedObject, PENamedObject, PEObject
public class Ellipsoid
extends BaseNamedGeodeticObject
implements PENamedObject, Cloneable, Equivalency

implements a geodetic ellipsoid having a semi-major and semi-minor axis. An ellipsoid is conceptually a surface of revolution created by revolving an ellipse on its minor axis.

geodeticInverse

public double geodeticInverse(Point3D fromPt,
                              Point3D toPt,
                              double[] azs)
Calculates the geodesic, returning the distance along with the azimuths at both points. The azimuths are returned azs[2] array with azs[0] being the azimuth from fromPt towards ToPt. And the azs[1] is the azimuth from toPt towards toPt. Note that these are generally never simply out of phase from one another (except for the simple cases).

Parameters:
fromPt - the start point (radians-longitude(X), latitude(Y))
toPt - the end point (radians-longitude(X), latitude(Y))
azs - the azimuths at the start point and end point (must be previously allocated) (radians)
Returns:
the distance in meters

geodeticDirect

public void geodeticDirect(Point3D fromPt,
                           double distance,
                           double az12,
                           Point3D toPt)
Performs a geodetic direct operation that results with a coordinate being calculated. Given a start point, an azimuth from that point, and a distance, the point is calculated along the surface of the ellipsoid.

Parameters:
fromPt - the from point (radians-longitude(X), latitude(Y))
distance - the distance (meters)
az12 - the azimuth (radians)
toPt - the computed point( must be previously allocated)(radians-longitude(X), latitude(Y))
